article.description: Breck Ruddick threw three touchdown passes, and Missouri State held on to beat Murray State 28-22 on Saturday.
article.headline: Ruddick's 3 TDs lift Missouri State over Murray St 28-22
article.linkText: Ruddick's 3 TDs lift Missouri State over Murray St 28-22
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. -- Breck Ruddick threw three touchdown passes, and Missouri State held on to beat Murray State 28-22 on Saturday. Murray State pulled within two when KD Humphries found Jordon Gandy for a 1-yard score with 1:46 left in the third quarter, but the 2-point attempt was no good, and Calan Crowder's 16-yard TD run pushed the Bears' lead to 28-19 midway through the fourth. Crowder rushed for 97 yards on 19 carries. Connor Mitchell kicked a 37-yard field goal for Murray State to make it a one-score game with 1:29 remaining, but Missouri State (2-0) was able to run the clock out. Murray State (0-2) got within three on Gandy's 55-yard scoring pass to Gandy in the second quarter, but Missouri State answered with an seven-play, 75-yard drive culminating in an 8-yard TD reception by Adam St. Peter to give the Bears a 21-10 lead.
